    <thetext>Description:

Some of the Fedora deployments do not include open-vm-tools by default when being installed on a VMware platform. Anaconda 22.1-1 has a fix to detect the underlying platform and include the package group by default (http://pkgs.fedoraproject.org/cgit/rpms/anaconda.git/commit/?h=f23&amp;id=2d13a8eaff16637e31f6b633c3a2cfd0f51b10c7). Anaconda was fixed as part of RHBZ#884385. We need to create a new package group called &quot;platform-vmware&quot; for VMware specific packages and place open-vm-tools package &quot;open-vm-tools&quot; in it.

Packages to be added: open-vm-tools

Comps group:  platform-vmware

Default: Yes

Mandatory: No

Visible: May be yes, for users to be able to override?

Multi-lib: Don&apos;t know

Need to be present for arches: Don&apos;t know</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
